## Security Checklist

Before committing code:

- [ ] No hardcoded sensitive information
- [ ] All sensitive information stored in `.env` files (not in config files)
- [ ] All `.env*` files in `.gitignore`
- [ ] No API keys/secrets use `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix
- [ ] Client-side code never directly accesses API keys
- [ ] Logs do not contain sensitive information
- [ ] **Backend (API Routes / Functions):** Do not return `error.message` or stack in HTTP responses; return generic messages only; log full error server-side for debugging
- [ ] **Frontend:** Never directly display `error.message` or `response.message` from backend
- [ ] Always use error code mapping (`ErrorMessages[code]`) for known API errors
- [ ] Provide generic fallback messages for unknown errors
- [ ] Show detailed error information only in development mode